  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2014-04-28", 
    "text": "Stop Wasteful Federal Bonuses Act of 2014 - Prohibits a federal agency from awarding a bonus to any employee for five years after the end of a fiscal year in which the Inspector General of the agency or another senior ethics official\u00a0or the Comptroller General (GAO) makes an adverse\u00a0finding relating to the employee. Requires repayment of a\u00a0bonus awarded in any year in which an adverse finding is made."
  }, 
